init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're immortal, but you're also a monster.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You decide to go on a road trip to find the people who took the drug, to apologize for your resentment.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You find your family, but they are not the same.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They don't care about you, and they don't care about each other.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You decide to stay with them, and try to help them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You try to show them that they can still feel love, and that they can still care about each other.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You try to teach them how to be human again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the only one who can help them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the only one who can teach them how to be human again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the only one who can save them.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the only one who can save yourself.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You bury them with the note that you wrote to them, and leave.
